ENTRY       EC 1.16.1.10                Enzyme
NAME        ferric-chelate reductase [NAD(P)H];
            ferric reductase (ambiguous)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Oxidizing metal ions;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     Fe(II)-siderophore:NAD(P)+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    2 Fe(II)-siderophore + NAD(P)+ + H+ = 2 Fe(III)-siderophore + NAD(P)H
SUBSTRATE   Fe(II)-siderophore;
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
PRODUCT     Fe(III)-siderophore;
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005]
COMMENT     A flavoprotein. The enzyme catalyses the reduction of bound ferric iron in a variety of iron chelators (siderophores), resulting in the release of ferrous iron. The enzyme from the hyperthermophilic archaeon Archaeoglobus fulgidus is not active with uncomplexed Fe(III). cf. EC 1.16.1.7, ferric-chelate reductase (NADH) and EC 1.16.1.9, ferric-chelate reductase (NADPH).
